  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to bleaching white Vans:\n\nMaterials needed:\n- Bleach\n- Water\n- Protective gloves\n- Old toothbrush\n- Bucket or large container\n- Soft cloth\n- Paper towels\n\nSteps:\n1. Prepare your workspace\n- Work in a well-ventilated area\n- Wear protective gloves\n- Protect surfaces with newspaper or plastic\n\n2. Remove laces\n- Take out shoelaces to bleach separately or replace\n\n3. Mix bleach solution\n- Use 1 part bleach to 5 parts water\n- Don't use pure bleach, as it can damage the shoes\n\n4. Clean shoes\n- Use a soft brush or toothbrush to remove loose dirt\n- Dip brush in bleach solution and scrub gently\n- Focus on stained areas\n\n5. Soak or spot clean\n- For overall whitening: Soak shoes briefly in solution\n- For spot cleaning: Apply solution directly to stains\n\n6. Rinse thoroughly\n- Wash off bleach with clean water\n- Use a damp cloth to remove residue\n\n7. Dry completely\n- Air dry at room temperature\n- Avoid direct sunlight or heat\n\n8. Optional: Touch up with white shoe polish or whitener",
